The '''Association of Arctic Expedition Cruise Operators''' (AECO) is a voluntary cooperative organization of cruise lines largely working in the European arctic, including [[Greenland]] and [[Svalbard]].  AECO establishes guidelines for its members that cover passenger safety, environmental protection issues and ethical interactions with [[Indigenous peoples|indigenous]] populations.<ref name="LuĘckMaher2010">{{cite book|last1=LuĘck|first1=Michael|last2=Maher|first2=Patrick Timothy|last3=Stewart|first3=Emma Julie|title=Cruise Tourism in Polar Regions: Promoting Environmental and Social Sustainability?|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SnmAK5J76iIC&pg=PA143|accessdate=12 June 2013|year=2010|publisher=Earthscan|isbn=9781849776394|pages=143–}}</ref><ref name="HillGale2012">{{cite book|last1=Hill|first1=Jennifer|last2=Gale|first2=Tim|title=Ecotourism and Environmental Sustainability: Principles and Practice|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MrHUzT_k8_EC&pg=PA101|accessdate=12 June 2013|date=2012-11-28|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=9781409488194|pages=101–}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://seattletimes.com/html/travel/2004042125_polarcruise02.html|title=Are polar cruises safe? Not all ships are equal|last=Woodard|first=Colin|date=December 2, 2007|work=[[Seattle Times]]|accessdate=12 June 2013}}</ref>

